02:47.407 --> 02:49.325
Come on, Peter.

02:50.078 --> 02:53.082
Wake up. Peter. Wake up.

02:54.507 --> 02:55.934
Here's your suit.

03:00.153 --> 03:02.855
Do you know if your sister
slept in her room last night?

03:04.328 --> 03:05.429
I don't know.

03:08.369 --> 03:09.855
Come on, Peter. Get up.

03:32.443 --> 03:35.756
Oh, Charlie.
For God's sake, come on!

03:38.173 --> 03:40.143
It was freezing last night!

03:40.513 --> 03:42.238
That's how you get pneumonia.

03:42.419 --> 03:43.795
That's okay.

03:44.069 --> 03:46.269
Okay, come on.
Let's go. We're late.

03:46.318 --> 03:48.119
Your mother's
in the car already.

03:58.748 --> 04:00.993
Um...

04:01.998 --> 04:07.064
It's heartening to see so many
strange new faces here today.

04:07.846 --> 04:11.863
Um, I know my mom
would be very touched

04:12.267 --> 04:15.038
and probably a little
suspicious...

04:15.210 --> 04:18.930
um, to see this turnout. So.

04:22.990 --> 04:27.495
My mother was a very secretive
and private woman.

04:27.725 --> 04:29.536
She had private rituals,

04:29.622 --> 04:32.626
private friends,
private anxieties.

04:33.282 --> 04:34.698
It honestly feels
like a betrayal

04:34.700 --> 04:36.950
just to be standing here
talking about her.

04:43.758 --> 04:46.361
<i>She was a very difficult woman
to read.</i>

04:47.286 --> 04:50.172
<i>If you ever thought you knew
what was going on with her,</i>

04:50.213 --> 04:52.549
<i>and God forbid
you tried to confront that.</i>

04:56.407 --> 04:57.792
<i>But when her life
was unpolluted,</i>

04:57.862 --> 05:00.298
<i>she could be
the sweetest, warmest,</i>

05:00.346 --> 05:02.353
<i>most loving person
in the world.</i>

05:04.116 --> 05:06.107
She was also
incredibly stubborn,

05:06.156 --> 05:08.713
which maybe, explains me.

05:10.729 --> 05:13.332
You could always count on her
to always have the answer.

05:14.871 --> 05:17.401
And if she ever was mistaken,

05:17.461 --> 05:19.710
and well,
that was your opinion...

05:19.745 --> 05:24.562
And you were wrong.

05:48.085 --> 05:49.763
There aren't nuts in that?

05:50.279 --> 05:51.747
- No.
- Good.

05:53.501 --> 05:55.129
Does that have nuts? 'Cause
we don't have the EpiPen.

05:55.131 --> 05:56.143
I know.

06:23.833 --> 06:27.923
Hello, Rexy! Good dog.

06:27.969 --> 06:29.534
Shoes off, everybody.

06:29.828 --> 06:32.093
Charlie, shoes off.

06:40.325 --> 06:41.763
It does feel weird.

06:43.130 --> 06:44.331
Yeah.

06:45.759 --> 06:47.181
Should I be sadder?

06:47.976 --> 06:51.659
You should be
whatever you are. It'll come.

07:13.242 --> 07:15.249
Hey, how's it going?

07:15.383 --> 07:16.993
Mmm, just working.

07:18.053 --> 07:20.381
Taking a break
from avoiding the show.

07:25.385 --> 07:29.312
So, you still toiling away
at the hospice?

07:29.720 --> 07:32.456
Yeah, between this
and the, uh, preschool.

07:34.267 --> 07:37.252
So what's our deadline now?
Seven months?

07:37.819 --> 07:40.589
- Six and a half.
- Ooh, coming up.

07:42.105 --> 07:43.941
Any ideas for titles?

07:51.748 --> 07:52.783
Come in.

07:53.920 --> 07:54.955
Hey...

07:55.139 --> 07:57.107
- Goodnight, kiddo.
- Goodnight.

07:59.857 --> 08:03.264
Are you, uh... Are you feeling
okay about everything?

08:03.350 --> 08:05.226
Yeah. Fine.

08:05.975 --> 08:07.342
A little sad?

08:08.320 --> 08:10.694
Mmm...

08:10.791 --> 08:13.921
Yeah, I get it. I know.

08:14.242 --> 08:15.901
- Goodnight.
- Night.

08:15.957 --> 08:17.258
Love you.

08:32.453 --> 08:33.488
Who's this?

08:36.173 --> 08:37.506
That's Grandma?

08:48.423 --> 08:50.488
You know
you were her favorite, right?

08:52.029 --> 08:53.931
Even when
you were a little baby,

08:53.933 --> 08:54.656
she wouldn't let me feed you

08:54.658 --> 08:56.330
because she needed
to feed you.

08:56.519 --> 08:58.046
Drove me crazy.

08:59.070 --> 09:01.080
She wanted me to be a boy.

09:05.678 --> 09:08.082
You know, I was a tomboy
when I was growing up.

09:08.646 --> 09:12.909
I hated dresses
and dolls and pink.

09:14.703 --> 09:16.538
Who's gonna take care of me?

09:16.755 --> 09:19.696
Um, excuse me.

09:19.698 --> 09:21.797
You don't think
I'm gonna take care of you?

09:23.210 --> 09:24.758
But when you die.

09:27.766 --> 09:29.039
Well, then...

09:30.117 --> 09:31.818
Dad will take care of you.

09:33.076 --> 09:34.463
Or Peter.

09:51.238 --> 09:53.040
You never cried as a baby.

09:54.911 --> 09:56.412
You know that?

09:58.133 --> 09:59.902
Even when you were born.

10:08.922 --> 10:11.019
Did you feel
like you wanted to cry today?

10:16.122 --> 10:18.292
You think it might feel
like a relief?

10:43.646 --> 10:45.049
Goodnight, sweetheart.

12:37.005 --> 12:38.252
Mom?

13:19.092 --> 13:21.262
I just scared myself
in the workshop.

13:23.050 --> 13:24.851
With... With what?

13:30.025 --> 13:31.094
No.

13:52.976 --> 13:54.144
Are you done?

13:56.079 --> 13:57.314
Almost.

13:58.546 --> 14:01.996
So, maybe we finish the toy
after the quiz.

14:02.077 --> 14:03.244
What do you think?

14:05.202 --> 14:06.697
- Okay.
- Okay.

14:15.298 --> 14:17.703
Oh, my God! What was that?

14:31.257 --> 14:33.007
So, if we go by the rule

14:33.061 --> 14:36.417
that the hero is undone
by his fatal flaw,

14:36.468 --> 14:39.039
what is Heracles' flaw?

14:40.235 --> 14:41.437
Arrogance.

14:41.491 --> 14:44.029
Okay. Why?

14:44.447 --> 14:47.217
Because he literally refuses
to look at all the signs

14:47.273 --> 14:50.179
that are literally handed
to him the entire play.

14:50.746 --> 14:52.857
Okay, interesting.

14:52.908 --> 14:55.169
So he thinks he has control.

14:55.245 --> 14:56.668
But let's all remember,

14:56.747 --> 14:59.802
Sophocles wrote the oracle
so that it was unconditional,

14:59.865 --> 15:03.831
meaning, Heracles never had
any choice, right?

15:03.900 --> 15:06.727
So does that make it
more tragic or less tragic

15:06.783 --> 15:09.036
that if he has a choice?

15:09.106 --> 15:11.081
- Less.
- Okay.

15:11.178 --> 15:13.081
- Why?
- Because.

15:15.884 --> 15:17.652
Care to weigh in, Peter?

15:19.352 --> 15:21.347
Um, about which part?

15:23.599 --> 15:24.689
I think it's more tragic

15:24.691 --> 15:26.467
because if it's all
just inevitable,

15:26.469 --> 15:28.888
then that means that
the characters had no hope.

15:28.997 --> 15:29.798
They never had hope

15:29.800 --> 15:31.688
because they're all just,
like, hopeless.

15:31.787 --> 15:32.649
They're all like pawns

15:32.651 --> 15:35.209
in this horrible,
hopeless machine.

16:49.242 --> 16:51.211
- Hello!
- Hi!

17:33.671 --> 17:35.206
Did you go up
in my mom's room?

17:36.451 --> 17:37.585
No.

17:38.371 --> 17:40.172
Mmm. Door was open.

17:46.186 --> 17:47.186
Hello?

17:47.218 --> 17:48.800
Sorry. I know it's irrational.

17:48.864 --> 17:50.566
- No problem.
- Thank you.

17:51.571 --> 17:53.718
Hey, Dad. It's the cemetery.

17:54.033 --> 17:55.169
About what?

17:56.027 --> 17:57.227
Let me see.

17:57.927 --> 18:00.647
Hello? Yes.

18:07.918 --> 18:09.418
What does that mean?

18:10.166 --> 18:11.502
Desecrated?

18:16.070 --> 18:17.773
But it's only been a week.

18:21.198 --> 18:24.151
Yes, okay, yes. Sure.

18:24.282 --> 18:25.723
All right. I understand.
Yes...

18:25.779 --> 18:28.688
Uh, why don't I call you back?
Yes. Goodbye.

18:28.729 --> 18:29.865
What was it?

18:31.717 --> 18:34.138
Uh, just some billing crap.

18:35.422 --> 18:37.846
Okay, well, I'm, uh...
I'm gonna go see a movie.

18:38.974 --> 18:40.080
Okay.

19:07.553 --> 19:08.265
He would say,

19:08.267 --> 19:11.635
"I'm a burden, I'm a burden,
I'm a burden."

19:15.789 --> 19:18.082
And I would tell him, "No, no."

19:25.049 --> 19:27.958
But yes, he was a burden.

19:28.663 --> 19:31.774
Now we've set aside
some time for any newcomers

19:31.826 --> 19:33.611
who might like to speak.

19:33.688 --> 19:35.387
So, anyone.

19:35.448 --> 19:38.854
If it's your first
or second time with us,

19:38.893 --> 19:40.495
the floor is open.

19:44.209 --> 19:47.103
Yes. Would you like to...

19:47.171 --> 19:48.413
Maybe not.

19:48.878 --> 19:51.699
Okay. No pressure.

19:59.354 --> 20:00.488
My name's Annie.

20:00.715 --> 20:02.021
Hi, Annie.

20:03.703 --> 20:05.562
My mom died a week ago.

20:05.853 --> 20:09.043
So I'm just here
for trying it.

20:10.102 --> 20:12.639
I have a lot of resistance
to things like this,

20:12.757 --> 20:15.798
but I came to these
a couple years ago.

20:15.839 --> 20:18.950
Well, I was forced to come
and I guess it, um...

20:20.368 --> 20:22.339
I guess it helped. So, um...

20:25.330 --> 20:28.925
My mom was old and she wasn't
all together there at the end.

20:29.007 --> 20:31.353
And we were pretty much
estranged before that,

20:31.355 --> 20:34.279
so it really wasn't
a huge blow.

20:34.572 --> 20:39.817
But I did love her.

20:41.250 --> 20:42.701
And she didn't have
an easy life.

20:42.752 --> 20:45.891
She had DID, which became
extreme at the end.

20:46.110 --> 20:47.577
And dementia.

20:47.679 --> 20:51.717
And my father died when I was
a baby from starvation,

20:51.799 --> 20:54.619
um, because he had
psychotic depression

20:54.689 --> 20:55.417
and he starved himself,

20:55.419 --> 20:57.687
which I'm sure was just
as pleasant as it sounds.

20:57.744 --> 20:59.278
And then there's my brother.

20:59.428 --> 21:01.330
My older brother
had schizophrenia

21:01.394 --> 21:02.661
and when he was 16

21:02.701 --> 21:04.438
he hanged himself
in my mother's bedroom

21:04.500 --> 21:06.150
and of course
the suicide note blamed her

21:06.186 --> 21:09.590
accusing her of putting people
inside him. So.

21:13.336 --> 21:15.272
That was my mom's life.

21:27.742 --> 21:28.974
And then she lived
in our house

21:28.976 --> 21:30.691
at the end before hospice.

21:30.727 --> 21:32.247
We weren't even talking
before that.

21:32.315 --> 21:34.312
I mean, we were
and then we weren't.

21:34.601 --> 21:36.208
And then we were.

21:39.117 --> 21:40.674
She's completely manipulative.

21:40.710 --> 21:44.099
Until my husband finally
enforced a no-contact rule,

21:44.157 --> 21:46.422
which lasted until I got
pregnant with my daughter.

21:46.517 --> 21:47.589
I didn't let her
anywhere near me

21:47.591 --> 21:49.245
when I had my first, my son,

21:49.298 --> 21:51.114
which is why I gave her
my daughter,

21:51.116 --> 21:53.580
who she immediately
stabbed her hooks into.

21:53.956 --> 21:56.676
And I just...
I felt guilty again.

21:56.719 --> 21:58.158
I felt guilty again.

21:58.415 --> 21:59.458
When she got sick,

21:59.460 --> 22:01.701
not that she was really even
my mom at the end,

22:01.703 --> 22:06.342
and not that she would ever
feel guilty about anything.

22:10.949 --> 22:14.500
And I just don't want to put
any more stress on my family.

22:16.810 --> 22:19.134
I'm not even really sure
if they could...

22:20.713 --> 22:22.548
Could give me that support.

22:26.045 --> 22:27.881
And I just...
I just feel like...

22:31.387 --> 22:33.445
I just sometimes
feel like it's all ruined.

22:36.245 --> 22:40.418
And then I realize
that I am to blame.

22:43.029 --> 22:44.063
Or not that I'm to blame,

22:44.108 --> 22:48.881
but I am blamed! I'm...

22:50.069 --> 22:53.756
And what do you think
you feel blamed for?

22:57.116 --> 22:58.482
I don't know.

23:02.503 --> 23:03.647
<i>Hey, what's going on in town</i>

23:03.649 --> 23:05.468
<i>anyway, Mister?
A convention or something?</i>

23:05.470 --> 23:06.178
<i>What?</i>

23:06.180 --> 23:07.410
<i>Well, those clothes
you're wearing.</i>

23:07.412 --> 23:08.388
<i>I talked to a guy this morning</i>

23:08.390 --> 23:10.355
<i>who was wearing
the same kind of outfit.</i>

23:10.472 --> 23:12.747
<i>Maybe it's the guy
you're looking for, huh?</i>

23:12.749 --> 23:14.116
<i>You spoke to him?</i>

23:14.467 --> 23:16.486
<i>What did he tell you?
Where did he go?</i>

23:16.558 --> 23:17.883
<i>Hey, what's the matter
with you?</i>

23:17.907 --> 23:19.124
<i>Hey, take your hands off me.</i>

23:19.148 --> 23:20.642
<i>You will tell me
what he said to you!</i>

23:20.666 --> 23:21.698
<i>Well why should I?</i>

23:21.749 --> 23:23.349
<i>Hey, who do you think
you are anyway?</i>

23:25.524 --> 23:26.924
<i>He came in
with the dog tags!</i>

23:27.031 --> 23:28.197
<i>Wanted to know
about the address</i>

23:28.199 --> 23:29.408
<i>and I told him how to find it.</i>

23:29.448 --> 23:30.449
Where?

25:35.511 --> 25:39.169
Hey, um, do you think
I could maybe borrow

25:39.171 --> 25:40.705
one of the cars tonight?

25:40.965 --> 25:43.392
Why? Where are you going?

25:43.569 --> 25:46.303
Oh, just like
a school barbecue thing.

25:46.518 --> 25:48.289
Oh, so you're not eating
with us?

25:48.452 --> 25:50.174
No, I was still gonna
eat here.

25:50.298 --> 25:51.715
Well, you can eat there
if you want. I just didn't...

25:51.717 --> 25:54.339
No, no, no. I'm gonna
eat here. I just, I...

25:54.394 --> 25:57.097
Just be going to hang out.

25:59.682 --> 26:00.884
No drinking?

26:02.407 --> 26:05.445
We're not even old enough
to get drinks if we wanted to.

26:05.752 --> 26:08.621
Well, that's a crock. I'm just
asking if you're drinking.

26:09.035 --> 26:10.669
Well, I just answered no.

26:12.414 --> 26:14.093
You gonna take your sister?

26:15.595 --> 26:18.454
Uh... Does she want to go?

26:19.087 --> 26:21.756
Have you asked her?

26:25.443 --> 26:26.611
Charlie?

26:57.021 --> 26:58.101
Charlie!

27:00.217 --> 27:04.427
I mean, what are you doing?
Leaving the house barefoot?

27:04.625 --> 27:05.649
Are you some kind of idiot?

27:05.651 --> 27:08.358
You can't roam around
with no shoes and no coat.

27:08.528 --> 27:10.294
- I want Grandma.
- Oh.

27:10.902 --> 27:13.428
Oh, what?
You're angry with me now?

27:16.837 --> 27:19.276
You are going to this...
Hey, socks off.

27:19.416 --> 27:21.219
You're going to this party
with your brother.

27:21.883 --> 27:22.819
What party?

27:22.821 --> 27:25.532
Some school hangout
with other kids.

27:27.148 --> 27:27.867
That's okay.

27:27.869 --> 27:30.990
No, it's not okay.
You're going.

27:31.114 --> 27:32.586
- Why?
- Because it'll be fun.

27:32.642 --> 27:34.574
Because you'll get to hang out
with other kids.

27:34.637 --> 27:35.850
- With who?
- With your...

27:35.902 --> 27:37.602
With your brother.
With other kids.

27:42.940 --> 27:44.524
- Fine.
- Good. You're going.

27:44.556 --> 27:46.559
- She's going with you.
- Great.

27:46.613 --> 27:48.455
Now this really means
no drinking.

27:48.524 --> 27:50.293
Yeah, I really wasn't
going to.

29:26.665 --> 29:28.144
<i>Whoa. Hi.</i>

29:29.571 --> 29:30.873
Oh. Hi.

29:31.533 --> 29:32.868
How's the party?

29:34.069 --> 29:36.232
Why? You wanna know
if you should come?

29:36.629 --> 29:38.643
Uh, yeah. What do ya think?

29:41.108 --> 29:42.443
Either way.

29:45.096 --> 29:47.465
Hey, do you happen
to smoke at all?

29:47.505 --> 29:49.140
I have really good weed.

29:55.554 --> 29:57.823
- The other room has a bong.
- Sick.

30:03.363 --> 30:04.902
Do you wanna wait out here
for a second?

30:04.926 --> 30:06.967
- No.
- Charlie, please, just...

30:07.032 --> 30:08.852
It'll be two minutes
and then we can hang out.

30:08.918 --> 30:11.866
You can draw.
Please, Charlie. I'm...

30:13.472 --> 30:15.610
Oh, shit, look. They're
giving out chocolate cake.

30:15.612 --> 30:16.869
Not to everyone.

30:16.871 --> 30:18.210
Yes to everyone. It's a party.

30:18.257 --> 30:20.252
- I don't know anyone.
- Nobody does.

30:20.307 --> 30:23.061
Just walk over and stand there
and they'll give you a piece.

30:23.118 --> 30:25.078
Hurry up. They're gonna
run out. Come on, Charlie.

30:30.762 --> 30:34.167
Hey, guys. Peter has weed.

30:58.063 --> 30:59.701
That was your sister downstairs?

31:00.014 --> 31:02.041
Yeah. Charlie.

31:03.964 --> 31:05.232
Is your sister hot?

31:08.035 --> 31:10.025
I actually saw her
drawing me last week.

31:10.230 --> 31:11.157
Oh, yeah?

31:11.225 --> 31:13.951
Yeah. She made me
look retarded.

31:14.256 --> 31:15.622
Yeah. That's Charlie.

31:44.936 --> 31:46.403
Peter?

31:46.592 --> 31:49.462
Charlie.

31:49.815 --> 31:52.085
What's up?

31:56.485 --> 31:57.787
Are you okay?

31:59.386 --> 32:01.256
It's hard to breathe.

32:02.918 --> 32:03.985
What do you mean?

32:05.179 --> 32:07.307
I think my throat's
getting bigger.

32:56.734 --> 32:58.894
It's okay, Charlie.
We're almost at the hospital, okay?

33:16.878 --> 33:18.880
Charlie!

34:38.793 --> 34:40.117
You okay.

34:43.246 --> 34:44.380
Okay.

35:52.622 --> 35:54.688
Okay, good. They're home.

35:55.351 --> 35:56.418
Good.

36:53.427 --> 36:55.587
I'm running out
for some balsam wood.

36:55.589 --> 36:56.815
You want anything?

36:56.861 --> 36:59.317
I'm good, sweetheart.
Drive safe.

36:59.372 --> 37:01.998
Okay. Back in 20.

37:39.563 --> 37:43.020
Oh, my God! Oh, my God!

37:47.648 --> 37:51.834
Oh, no. I can't, I can't...

37:51.964 --> 37:57.378
I just want to die!

38:03.443 --> 38:06.152
Oh, God. It hurts too much!

38:06.154 --> 38:08.292
I just need to die!

38:12.881 --> 38:16.243
Charlie!

38:20.322 --> 38:24.185
Oh, God.

38:30.258 --> 38:33.469
Oh, Charlie!

42:06.125 --> 42:08.667
Hey, are you guys friends
with Becky on Facebook?

42:09.269 --> 42:10.971
You're friends with Becky?

42:11.558 --> 42:14.096
I said "Facebook friends."

42:15.017 --> 42:16.813
But seriously,
you see her statuses, bro?

42:16.815 --> 42:18.602
Oh, my God, dude, I know.

42:18.649 --> 42:21.136
- Like, every ten seconds.
- For real.

42:21.182 --> 42:24.937
Oh, dude, what about, uh,
fucking... Let me hit that.

42:25.000 --> 42:27.070
- Brian?
- Brian and his girlfriend.

42:27.143 --> 42:28.379
He calls her something...

42:28.426 --> 42:30.546
He calls her something really
goofy, dude. What does he...

42:30.570 --> 42:31.668
Oh, he calls her princess.

42:34.367 --> 42:36.460
Who fucking calls
their girlfriend "princess"?

42:36.509 --> 42:38.175
What the fuck?

42:38.229 --> 42:39.011
Dude, he's like,

42:39.042 --> 42:41.742
"I'm picking up
my princess from the airport.

42:41.797 --> 42:44.001
Fucking eating cous...
What the fuck.

42:44.064 --> 42:44.831
It's couscous.

